      "id": "752gMr",
      "text": "An **Energy Audit** is the essential first step to properly sizing your battery bank and charging sources. The goal is to calculate your total daily power consumption, expressed in **Amp-Hours (Ah)**.\n\n### Performing the Audit:\n1.  **List all DC Devices:** Compile a comprehensive list of every electrical device on board (lights, fridge, navigation equipment, pumps, fans, etc.).\n2.  **Determine Current Draw:** Find the current draw (in Amps) for each item. Use manufacturer specifications, an inline ammeter, or a clamp meter for accurate measurement.\n3.  **Estimate Daily Usage:** Record or estimate the total number of hours each device will run per 24-hour period.\n\n### The Calculation:\nMultiply the device's **Amps** by the **Hours of Use** to get its daily **Amp-Hour** consumption. Sum the results from all devices to determine your total daily Ah consumption, which is the minimum capacity your battery bank must supply.",
